teaching in wallenberg hall teaching in wallenberg hall teaching in wallenberg hall the spaces in wallenberg hall have been uniquely designed to facilitate exploring teaching and learning in the context of current information and media technologies explore the classrooms and resources tales out of school the wallenberg hall crew are committed to communicating our experiences and findings to anyone interested in education a collection of papers presentations and short anecdotes have collected and are available on our research findings page a selection of clips from in depth interviews with wallenberg faculty are also available arranged by topic reserving teaching spaces in wallenberg hall the first floor classrooms of wallenberg hall and the peter wallenberg learning theater provide resource rich learning spaces with great space flexibility to enable faculty to experiment with classroom activities not possible in other classroom facilities events for workshops or speaking events see the registrar's events site teaching and learning classroom resources research programs about wallenberg hall help & assistance
